WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.630 --> 00:00:53.090
- Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:53.170 --> 00:00:54.880
Show me its arm.

3
00:00:54.969 --> 00:00:57.840
- She bears the mark.
- No!

4
00:01:00.509 --> 00:01:04.020
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:06.439 --> 00:01:08.560
- Please. help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:08.650 --> 00:01:11.439
They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:19.319 --> 00:01:23.870
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

8
00:01:32.379 --> 00:01:34.959
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

9
00:01:59.319 --> 00:02:01.819
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

10
00:02:01.909 --> 00:02:04.829
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

11
00:02:04.909 --> 00:02:09.750
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

12
00:02:09.830 --> 00:02:12.250
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

13
00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:15.710
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

14
00:02:15.759 --> 00:02:17.879
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

15
00:02:17.969 --> 00:02:20.050
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

16
00:02:20.129 --> 00:02:23.719
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

17
00:05:50.930 --> 00:05:52.930
Dada! Dada!

18
00:05:56.350 --> 00:05:59.649
- Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

19
00:06:00.899 --> 00:06:04.149
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

20
00:06:04.189 --> 00:06:06.149
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

21
00:06:06.189 --> 00:06:08.490
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

22
00:06:13.490 --> 00:06:16.040
Come on.

23
00:06:18.370 --> 00:06:21.420
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

24
00:06:21.500 --> 00:06:24.420
But. Dada. it's a baby.

25
00:06:24.500 --> 00:06:29.300
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

26
00:06:29.379 --> 00:06:32.930
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

27
00:06:33.009 --> 00:06:35.350
Daikinis are big.

28
00:06:35.389 --> 00:06:38.519
Giants who live far away.

29
00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:40.899
Oh. she's so cute.

30
00:06:40.980 --> 00:06:45.019
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

31
00:06:45.069 --> 00:06:50.319
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

32
00:06:50.399 --> 00:06:52.319
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

33
00:06:52.370 --> 00:06:56.540
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

34
00:06:56.620 --> 00:07:00.079
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

35
00:07:01.620 --> 00:07:05.459
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

36
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:07.509
Baaa!

37
00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.430
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

38
00:07:14.509 --> 00:07:16.509
Where did you
get these seeds?

39
00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:19.350
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:19.430 --> 00:07:23.350
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:23.439 --> 00:07:27.019
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:27.069 --> 00:07:30.529
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:30.610 --> 00:07:33.660
There's no law against that.

44
00:07:33.740 --> 00:07:38.910
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

45
00:07:38.949 --> 00:07:41.290
Magic?
You'll need magic...

46
00:07:41.370 --> 00:07:43.750
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:45.790 --> 00:07:51.300
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

48
00:07:53.509 --> 00:07:57.259
Baaa-

49
00:08:00.389 --> 00:08:03.389
Oh. you're lovely.

50
00:08:03.439 --> 00:08:05.439
Yes. you are.

51
00:08:05.519 --> 00:08:09.980
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

52
00:08:10.029 --> 00:08:14.949
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

53
00:08:15.029 --> 00:08:17.779
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

54
00:08:17.829 --> 00:08:22.579
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

55
00:08:22.660 --> 00:08:24.709
There we are. Come on.

56
00:08:24.790 --> 00:08:27.420
Hey. I will not be ignored!

57
00:08:27.500 --> 00:08:31.170
Mims? Ranon?

58
00:08:42.179 --> 00:08:44.309
You're gonna be all clean.

59
00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:54.279
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

60
00:08:54.360 --> 00:08:56.950
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

61
00:08:57.029 --> 00:08:59.830
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

62
00:08:59.909 --> 00:09:02.830
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

63
00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:05.919
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

64
00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:10.039
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

65
00:09:10.129 --> 00:09:12.169
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

66
00:09:12.259 --> 00:09:16.009
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

67
00:09:16.049 --> 00:09:19.350
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

68
00:09:22.100 --> 00:09:25.769
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

69
00:09:25.850 --> 00:09:28.649
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

70
00:09:36.279 --> 00:09:39.740
Dada. she likes you.

71
00:09:46.750 --> 00:09:47.919
Bye.

72
00:09:47.919 --> 00:09:51.039
Bye.

73
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:55.009
Come on. kids. Let's go.

74
00:10:01.049 --> 00:10:04.639
I will now magic ally join the rings!

75
00:10:26.620 --> 00:10:29.210
Whoa-ah!

76
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:36.419
Thank you. son.

77
00:10:36.460 --> 00:10:41.509
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

78
00:10:56.690 --> 00:10:58.950
Give me a ripe one. Good.

79
00:11:05.159 --> 00:11:09.659
And now. for my final amazing feat.

80
00:11:09.750 --> 00:11:14.590
I will make this entire pig disappear!

81
00:11:22.639 --> 00:11:27.769
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

82
00:11:27.850 --> 00:11:33.480
Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

83
00:11:35.730 --> 00:11:38.149
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

84
00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:43.909
No!
Hey. come here. you!

85
00:11:48.330 --> 00:11:51.750
I had seen enough.

86
00:12:06.850 --> 00:12:10.139
Attention! The High Aldwin...

87
00:12:10.220 --> 00:12:13.139
- will now make his choice for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

88
00:12:13.190 --> 00:12:16.649
Bring forth the hopefuls.

89
00:12:16.730 --> 00:12:19.149
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

90
00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:22.990
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

91
00:12:23.070 --> 00:12:25.529
Is this a joke?

92
00:12:25.620 --> 00:12:30.080
Willow?

93
00:12:32.500 --> 00:12:37.960
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:42.590
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

95
00:12:42.669 --> 00:12:46.679
All that your require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:46.759 --> 00:12:50.850
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:50.929 --> 00:12:55.440
is in which finger?

98
00:13:37.399 --> 00:13:41.940
No apprentice this year!

99
00:14:02.340 --> 00:14:05.720
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:14:05.799 --> 00:14:08.720
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:19.559
Mims!

102
00:14:20.940 --> 00:14:23.070
Mims!

103
00:14:31.320 --> 00:14:36.159
- Mims!
- Dada-

104
00:14:37.409 --> 00:14:40.500
I'm scared. Dada!

105
00:14:50.799 --> 00:14:53.389
Come on!

106
00:15:11.029 --> 00:15:13.990
Vohnkar!

107
00:15:23.500 --> 00:15:26.419
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

108
00:15:28.759 --> 00:15:30.549
Dada! Dada!

109
00:15:33.889 --> 00:15:36.139
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

110
00:15:39.179 --> 00:15:42.980
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

111
00:15:50.360 --> 00:15:53.700
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

112
00:15:53.779 --> 00:15:56.779
I'm here.

113
00:16:00.870 --> 00:16:04.500
Oh. Kiaya.

114
00:16:04.580 --> 00:16:06.789
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

115
00:16:06.840 --> 00:16:09.710
We have to take her
to the village council.

116
00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:28.110
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

117
00:16:28.190 --> 00:16:30.570
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

118
00:16:30.649 --> 00:16:32.610
until they find what
they're looking for!

119
00:16:32.700 --> 00:16:35.950
- It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

120
00:16:36.029 --> 00:16:38.529
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

121
00:16:38.580 --> 00:16:43.710
- In the pit! In the pit!

122
00:16:43.789 --> 00:16:45.919
In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:49.299
- In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

124
00:16:49.379 --> 00:16:53.720
Willow Ufgood.

125
00:16:53.799 --> 00:16:56.259
Come forward.

126
00:17:01.929 --> 00:17:07.269
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

127
00:17:12.859 --> 00:17:15.029
A Daikini child.

128
00:17:15.109 --> 00:17:18.319
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

129
00:17:18.410 --> 00:17:19.490
Yeah!

130
00:17:19.579 --> 00:17:22.869
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

131
00:17:22.950 --> 00:17:25.579
This child is special!

132
00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:29.960
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

133
00:17:30.039 --> 00:17:33.089
All the way across
the great river...

134
00:17:33.170 --> 00:17:35.259
to the Daikini crossroads.

135
00:17:35.339 --> 00:17:40.049
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

136
00:17:40.099 --> 00:17:43.470
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

137
00:17:43.559 --> 00:17:46.519
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

138
00:17:48.099 --> 00:17:50.730
I nominate Willow Ufgood.

139
00:17:50.769 --> 00:17:53.319
No!

140
00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:56.950
I will consult the bones!

141
00:18:04.329 --> 00:18:09.829
The bones tell me... nothing.

142
00:18:11.500 --> 00:18:15.420
Do you have any love
for this child?

143
00:18:23.849 --> 00:18:28.309
Yes. Yes. I do.

144
00:18:28.390 --> 00:18:32.819
The bones have spoken!

145
00:18:32.859 --> 00:18:36.819
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

146
00:18:36.900 --> 00:18:40.990
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

147
00:18:41.069 --> 00:18:43.579
But you will need help.

148
00:18:43.660 --> 00:18:49.000
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

149
00:18:51.039 --> 00:18:55.170
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

150
00:18:55.210 --> 00:18:58.509
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

151
00:18:58.589 --> 00:19:01.049
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

152
00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:03.849
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

153
00:19:03.890 --> 00:19:07.099
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

154
00:19:15.109 --> 00:19:17.690
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

155
00:19:17.779 --> 00:19:21.160
And according to the bones...

156
00:19:21.240 --> 00:19:24.619
- Bh-
- That leader is...

157
00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:26.119
...you. Burglekutt!

158
00:19:26.119 --> 00:19:27.119
you. Burglekutt!

159
00:19:27.200 --> 00:19:30.670
vohnkar!

160
00:19:30.750 --> 00:19:34.839
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

161
00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:40.220
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

162
00:19:40.299 --> 00:19:44.220
- Well. it was stupid.
- Just tell me.

163
00:19:44.259 --> 00:19:48.720
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

164
00:19:48.809 --> 00:19:53.559
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

165
00:19:53.599 --> 00:19:56.230
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

166
00:19:56.319 --> 00:20:01.150
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

167
00:20:03.109 --> 00:20:08.119
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

168
00:20:08.200 --> 00:20:12.210
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

169
00:20:15.289 --> 00:20:18.500
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

170
00:20:31.430 --> 00:20:35.900
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

171
00:20:35.980 --> 00:20:40.230
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

172
00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:44.359
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:20:44.450 --> 00:20:47.369
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:20:47.450 --> 00:20:50.869
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:20:50.950 --> 00:20:54.579
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:54.619 --> 00:20:57.789
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:57.839 --> 00:20:59.420
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:21:01.009 --> 00:21:06.339
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

179
00:21:09.430 --> 00:21:11.970
Good-bye. Dada.

180
00:21:14.019 --> 00:21:18.019
Go play!
Go on.

181
00:21:21.980 --> 00:21:25.529
We've never been apart.

182
00:21:26.569 --> 00:21:29.910
I miss you already.

183
00:21:31.240 --> 00:21:34.660
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

184
00:21:34.750 --> 00:21:36.670
I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:21:38.920 --> 00:21:41.670
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

186
00:21:43.710 --> 00:21:46.430
And... here.

187
00:21:48.549 --> 00:21:51.349
This will bring you luck.

188
00:22:04.529 --> 00:22:06.859
Good brave people!

189
00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:11.450
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:22:11.529 --> 00:22:16.250
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

191
00:22:19.750 --> 00:22:23.339
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

192
00:22:23.420 --> 00:22:26.970
Going the direction the bird is flying!

193
00:22:27.049 --> 00:22:30.970
Ooh.

194
00:22:31.049 --> 00:22:33.890
It's going back to the village!

195
00:22:35.730 --> 00:22:37.690
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:22:37.769 --> 00:22:40.019
Move out!

197
00:23:03.960 --> 00:23:07.420
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:23:07.509 --> 00:23:11.549
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

199
00:23:11.589 --> 00:23:14.099
The baby's sick.

200
00:23:18.059 --> 00:23:22.650
She's not sick!
Let me see.

201
00:23:22.730 --> 00:23:25.940
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

202
00:23:28.529 --> 00:23:31.609
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

203
00:23:33.950 --> 00:23:35.619
Clean me up.

204
00:23:39.289 --> 00:23:42.500
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

205
00:23:42.579 --> 00:23:46.500
- Sorsha. you're useless!
- I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

206
00:23:46.549 --> 00:23:48.759
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

207
00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:52.970
Ah. General Kael. at last.

208
00:23:53.049 --> 00:23:57.769
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

209
00:23:57.849 --> 00:24:01.559
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

210
00:24:01.640 --> 00:24:07.109
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

211
00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:09.150
that continues
somehow to elude her.

212
00:24:11.069 --> 00:24:13.029
The baby of the prophecy?

213
00:24:13.109 --> 00:24:16.529
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

214
00:24:16.619 --> 00:24:19.079
I must perform
the ritual that will...

215
00:24:19.160 --> 00:24:22.500
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

216
00:24:22.579 --> 00:24:25.329
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

217
00:24:25.380 --> 00:24:27.460
You'll do as I say. child.

218
00:24:33.890 --> 00:24:36.049
I read the signs.

219
00:24:36.140 --> 00:24:39.309
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

220
00:24:39.390 --> 00:24:43.559
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

221
00:24:59.289 --> 00:25:01.829
Move!

222
00:25:01.910 --> 00:25:03.869
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

223
00:25:08.170 --> 00:25:11.880
Come on!

224
00:25:21.470 --> 00:25:24.390
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

225
00:25:24.480 --> 00:25:27.440
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

226
00:25:27.519 --> 00:25:29.359
They couldn' t have gone far!

227
00:25:29.400 --> 00:25:32.400
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

228
00:25:39.779 --> 00:25:42.500
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

229
00:26:21.279 --> 00:26:25.450
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

230
00:26:41.890 --> 00:26:44.849
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

231
00:26:50.349 --> 00:26:52.859
What was that?

232
00:26:54.190 --> 00:26:56.990
Get the spears!

233
00:27:13.420 --> 00:27:15.380
Uhh. Uhh.

234
00:27:15.420 --> 00:27:19.299
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

235
00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:21.799
Do you understand?

236
00:27:21.890 --> 00:27:23.759
- Water.
- Yeah.

237
00:27:25.890 --> 00:27:27.890
Hurry up!

238
00:27:31.900 --> 00:27:34.819
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

239
00:27:34.900 --> 00:27:38.359
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

240
00:27:38.440 --> 00:27:40.859
We can't give her to him!

241
00:27:40.910 --> 00:27:44.869
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

242
00:27:44.950 --> 00:27:47.539
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

243
00:27:47.619 --> 00:27:50.500
He's looking right at us.

244
00:27:54.420 --> 00:27:56.420
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:27:56.460 --> 00:27:59.339
I'm somebody.

246
00:27:59.420 --> 00:28:03.759
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

247
00:28:05.599 --> 00:28:10.230
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

248
00:28:10.269 --> 00:28:14.230
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

249
00:28:14.309 --> 00:28:17.650
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

250
00:28:17.730 --> 00:28:21.109
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

251
00:28:21.150 --> 00:28:24.200
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

252
00:28:24.279 --> 00:28:29.369
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

253
00:28:29.450 --> 00:28:31.660
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

254
00:28:31.750 --> 00:28:35.170
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

255
00:28:35.250 --> 00:28:38.799
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

256
00:28:38.880 --> 00:28:42.799
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:28:42.880 --> 00:28:44.549
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

258
00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:46.720
Listen here. runt.

259
00:28:46.799 --> 00:28:50.769
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:28:50.849 --> 00:28:55.150
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

261
00:28:55.230 --> 00:28:58.609
You're gonna what?

262
00:29:02.490 --> 00:29:05.069
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

263
00:29:05.160 --> 00:29:07.160
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:29:10.829 --> 00:29:13.539
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:29:15.829 --> 00:29:19.420
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

266
00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:23.670
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:29:23.759 --> 00:29:26.430
just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:29:26.509 --> 00:29:29.970
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

269
00:29:30.009 --> 00:29:32.309
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:29:32.349 --> 00:29:37.309
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

271
00:29:37.400 --> 00:29:42.190
What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:29:42.279 --> 00:29:44.900
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:29:44.990 --> 00:29:49.779
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

274
00:29:49.869 --> 00:29:53.619
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:29:53.700 --> 00:29:57.460
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:03.380
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo.

277
00:30:03.460 --> 00:30:05.420
I'm really scared.

278
00:30:05.470 --> 00:30:08.339
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:30:08.390 --> 00:30:11.220
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:30:11.309 --> 00:30:13.980
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

281
00:30:14.059 --> 00:30:17.309
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

282
00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:19.940
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

283
00:30:48.549 --> 00:30:51.430
What was that?

284
00:30:54.809 --> 00:30:58.519
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:30:58.599 --> 00:31:02.730
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:31:02.769 --> 00:31:06.150
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

287
00:31:06.240 --> 00:31:09.700
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

288
00:31:09.779 --> 00:31:12.740
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

289
00:31:12.779 --> 00:31:16.250
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

290
00:31:16.289 --> 00:31:18.460
Good.

291
00:31:23.210 --> 00:31:25.509
Stop! Wait!

292
00:31:27.259 --> 00:31:30.009
Whoa!

293
00:31:35.470 --> 00:31:39.980
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:31:40.059 --> 00:31:42.559
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:31:42.650 --> 00:31:45.150
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:48.069
Humph.

297
00:31:48.150 --> 00:31:51.910
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

298
00:32:01.619 --> 00:32:06.380
I don't know why I try.

299
00:32:11.180 --> 00:32:14.430
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

300
00:32:14.509 --> 00:32:16.430
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

301
00:32:16.509 --> 00:32:18.890
What's that?

302
00:32:18.980 --> 00:32:22.940
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

303
00:32:23.019 --> 00:32:26.980
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

304
00:32:29.690 --> 00:32:33.490
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

305
00:32:37.829 --> 00:32:41.539
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

306
00:32:47.500 --> 00:32:51.420
Everything's gonna be all right.

307
00:32:54.759 --> 00:32:57.849
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

308
00:32:59.809 --> 00:33:02.190
Uh. pardon me.

309
00:33:02.230 --> 00:33:04.349
Uh-

310
00:33:09.980 --> 00:33:15.200
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

311
00:33:15.279 --> 00:33:18.200
Will you please
take care of her?

312
00:33:18.279 --> 00:33:22.710
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

313
00:33:24.119 --> 00:33:27.289
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

314
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.750
Well-

315
00:33:29.839 --> 00:33:34.380
- Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
- Nothing you wouldn't have done.

316
00:33:34.470 --> 00:33:36.839
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:33:36.930 --> 00:33:38.759
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

318
00:33:38.849 --> 00:33:40.349
What are you doing this far north?

319
00:33:40.430 --> 00:33:42.430
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

320
00:33:43.430 --> 00:33:44.769
The castle?

321
00:33:44.809 --> 00:33:47.269
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

322
00:33:47.359 --> 00:33:49.269
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

323
00:33:49.359 --> 00:33:51.609
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

324
00:33:51.730 --> 00:33:56.029
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

325
00:33:56.109 --> 00:33:58.069
You serve no one.

326
00:33:58.160 --> 00:34:00.410
Remember?

327
00:34:00.490 --> 00:34:03.700
Sit in your coffin and rot.

328
00:34:03.789 --> 00:34:06.829
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

329
00:34:06.920 --> 00:34:09.340
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

330
00:34:09.420 --> 00:34:12.050
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

331
00:34:12.130 --> 00:34:14.219
and stick it
on a pig pole!

332
00:34:31.730 --> 00:34:36.449
I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

333
00:34:40.449 --> 00:34:44.250
We're running out of food.

334
00:34:44.329 --> 00:34:47.960
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

335
00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:51.000
You know why?
Nobody cares.

336
00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:57.429
Except me.

337
00:34:57.510 --> 00:35:01.719
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

338
00:35:01.800 --> 00:35:05.769
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

339
00:35:05.849 --> 00:35:08.809
I believe he would. Willow.

340
00:35:08.900 --> 00:35:11.440
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

341
00:35:11.519 --> 00:35:16.739
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

342
00:35:16.820 --> 00:35:19.739
If I had somebody in my life.

343
00:35:19.820 --> 00:35:23.409
a little daughter. perhaps.

344
00:35:23.489 --> 00:35:26.750
I might have a reason
to go on living.

345
00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:32.789
You can't leave me
in here to die.

346
00:35:32.880 --> 00:35:35.920
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

347
00:35:49.230 --> 00:35:53.150
I feel better!

348
00:35:53.230 --> 00:35:56.940
- You've done the right thing! 
- Okay. All right. All right.

349
00:35:57.030 --> 00:36:01.489
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:36:01.570 --> 00:36:06.579
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:36:06.659 --> 00:36:08.699
Hee. hee. hee!

352
00:36:08.789 --> 00:36:13.670
Wheee!

353
00:36:13.750 --> 00:36:17.000
She likes me.

354
00:36:19.090 --> 00:36:21.469
Here are her changing rags.

355
00:36:21.550 --> 00:36:23.760
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

356
00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:28.099
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

357
00:36:29.809 --> 00:36:33.349
You wory too much. Peck.

358
00:36:33.440 --> 00:36:37.360
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

359
00:36:37.440 --> 00:36:43.199
Now listen. boys. Willow.
You've done the right thing.

360
00:36:43.280 --> 00:36:46.659
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

361
00:36:53.170 --> 00:36:57.420
Good-bye. little one.

362
00:37:06.139 --> 00:37:08.389
Please. take good care of her.

363
00:37:10.179 --> 00:37:13.019
I give you my word of honor!

364
00:37:19.690 --> 00:37:23.610
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

365
00:37:23.650 --> 00:37:27.909
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

366
00:37:27.989 --> 00:37:31.500
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:37:31.579 --> 00:37:33.829
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:37:33.920 --> 00:37:36.130
The heroes have come home."

369
00:37:36.210 --> 00:37:39.300
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:37:39.380 --> 00:37:43.630
Yeah. Medals.

371
00:37:43.670 --> 00:37:47.429
Meegosh-

372
00:37:49.309 --> 00:37:53.429
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

373
00:37:53.519 --> 00:37:57.809
There's nothing to worry about.

374
00:38:00.820 --> 00:38:03.110
Hyah! Ha!

375
00:38:03.190 --> 00:38:08.409
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

376
00:38:08.489 --> 00:38:12.250
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

377
00:38:12.329 --> 00:38:14.289
Stop! Wait! Come back!

378
00:38:14.369 --> 00:38:17.539
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

379
00:38:20.340 --> 00:38:23.590
- Ah!
- Ow!

380
00:38:23.670 --> 00:38:27.340
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

381
00:38:27.429 --> 00:38:30.760
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

382
00:38:31.760 --> 00:38:35.519
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

383
00:38:36.809 --> 00:38:38.860
We'll outrun 'em!

384
00:38:43.610 --> 00:38:47.699
Hey. ugly. wake up!-

385
00:38:47.780 --> 00:38:50.239
Huh?

386
00:38:50.280 --> 00:38:55.409
Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

387
00:38:55.449 --> 00:38:58.250
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

388
00:38:58.289 --> 00:39:00.250
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

389
00:39:00.289 --> 00:39:01.710
All right. you heard her!

390
00:39:01.789 --> 00:39:05.590
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

391
00:39:05.630 --> 00:39:08.010
You are mine to toy with.

392
00:39:08.090 --> 00:39:11.599
Forward!

393
00:39:11.679 --> 00:39:15.469
Gimme the rope.

394
00:39:15.559 --> 00:39:19.559
Where-
Where...

395
00:39:19.650 --> 00:39:21.940
did you get that baby?

396
00:39:21.980 --> 00:39:26.739
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

397
00:39:26.900 --> 00:39:30.070
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

398
00:39:30.110 --> 00:39:34.409
- And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

399
00:39:34.489 --> 00:39:36.579
Ahh-

400
00:39:38.829 --> 00:39:40.789
Yaah!

401
00:39:45.050 --> 00:39:48.300
You!

402
00:39:48.340 --> 00:39:53.429
Welcome to my kingdom.

403
00:39:59.599 --> 00:40:04.110
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:40:04.190 --> 00:40:07.440
Blora Danan told me.

405
00:40:07.489 --> 00:40:10.820
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

406
00:40:13.619 --> 00:40:19.159
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:40:19.250 --> 00:40:24.590
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

408
00:40:24.670 --> 00:40:29.590
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:40:29.670 --> 00:40:34.429
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:40:35.849 --> 00:40:40.809
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

411
00:40:40.889 --> 00:40:44.480
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

412
00:40:44.559 --> 00:40:48.820
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:40:48.860 --> 00:40:51.989
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:40:52.030 --> 00:40:55.829
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:40:55.989 --> 00:40:59.250
Blora. you don't want me.

416
00:40:59.329 --> 00:41:03.039
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:41:06.000 --> 00:41:08.630
Hello?

418
00:41:15.969 --> 00:41:19.389
Blora Danan must survive!

419
00:41:19.429 --> 00:41:24.309
She must fulfil her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:41:24.349 --> 00:41:27.230
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:41:27.269 --> 00:41:31.650
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

422
00:41:31.690 --> 00:41:36.280
of your village.
your children- everyone.

423
00:41:40.949 --> 00:41:44.460
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

424
00:41:44.539 --> 00:41:49.750
The choice is yours.

425
00:42:12.320 --> 00:42:16.570
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:42:16.610 --> 00:42:20.869
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:42:23.449 --> 00:42:27.000
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:42:27.079 --> 00:42:31.630
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:42:31.710 --> 00:42:35.170
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:42:35.260 --> 00:42:37.889
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:42:37.969 --> 00:42:40.889
I hope so.

432
00:42:40.969 --> 00:42:44.559
Listen. be careful.

433
00:42:50.650 --> 00:42:55.190
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:42:55.280 --> 00:42:58.739
- I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

435
00:42:58.820 --> 00:43:03.289
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

436
00:43:03.369 --> 00:43:06.460
- She's what?
- Exiled...

437
00:43:06.539 --> 00:43:10.380
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

438
00:43:10.460 --> 00:43:13.090
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

439
00:43:13.170 --> 00:43:15.760
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

440
00:43:15.840 --> 00:43:18.130
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

441
00:43:18.179 --> 00:43:20.849
So?

442
00:43:20.929 --> 00:43:23.719
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

443
00:43:23.809 --> 00:43:26.429
Don't play with that wand.

444
00:43:26.480 --> 00:43:29.059
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

445
00:43:29.150 --> 00:43:31.610
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

446
00:43:31.690 --> 00:43:34.440
- Not a stupid peck like you.

447
00:43:34.480 --> 00:43:37.650
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

448
00:43:37.739 --> 00:43:40.030
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

449
00:43:40.110 --> 00:43:42.619
- This way.
- This way?

450
00:43:42.699 --> 00:43:46.449
- That's what I said.
- This way.

451
00:43:46.500 --> 00:43:49.960
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

452
00:43:50.039 --> 00:43:52.750
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

453
00:44:03.179 --> 00:44:07.349
Take it up!

454
00:44:08.849 --> 00:44:13.110
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

455
00:44:13.190 --> 00:44:18.030
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

456
00:44:18.110 --> 00:44:21.699
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

457
00:44:59.440 --> 00:45:01.900
Excuse me? Excuse me.

458
00:45:01.949 --> 00:45:04.909
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

459
00:45:04.989 --> 00:45:06.869
Get out of here. peck!

460
00:45:06.949 --> 00:45:09.289
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

461
00:45:22.679 --> 00:45:26.599
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:45:26.639 --> 00:45:28.929
I could use
a love potion on her!

463
00:45:28.969 --> 00:45:32.809
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:45:32.889 --> 00:45:34.599
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

465
00:45:34.690 --> 00:45:38.070
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:45:42.239 --> 00:45:44.239
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:45:51.199 --> 00:45:54.960
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

468
00:45:57.250 --> 00:46:02.380
You are so beautiful!

469
00:46:02.469 --> 00:46:06.090
Your eyes! Your whiskers!

470
00:46:06.179 --> 00:46:08.800
- I have to kiss you!
- Rool!

471
00:46:08.889 --> 00:46:10.639
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:46:25.489 --> 00:46:27.699
Beer!

473
00:46:30.829 --> 00:46:32.949
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:46:37.539 --> 00:46:39.539
Hurry! Hurry!

475
00:46:39.630 --> 00:46:41.500
My husband's coming!

476
00:46:41.590 --> 00:46:43.630
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:46:43.710 --> 00:46:46.340
- How do I look?
- Not you!

478
00:46:47.550 --> 00:46:49.469
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:46:49.550 --> 00:46:51.809
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:46:51.849 --> 00:46:55.690
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:46:55.769 --> 00:46:57.980
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

482
00:46:58.059 --> 00:47:01.690
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:47:01.730 --> 00:47:04.570
Whoa!

484
00:47:04.650 --> 00:47:07.239
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:47:07.320 --> 00:47:09.699
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:47:09.739 --> 00:47:12.159
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:47:12.239 --> 00:47:14.500
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

488
00:47:14.539 --> 00:47:16.659
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:47:16.750 --> 00:47:19.500
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

490
00:47:19.579 --> 00:47:21.420
How do you do?

491
00:47:21.500 --> 00:47:23.880
Hilda! Ooh.

492
00:47:23.920 --> 00:47:26.050
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:47:26.130 --> 00:47:28.760
Hey! Give her back!

494
00:47:28.840 --> 00:47:31.219
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:47:31.300 --> 00:47:34.219
They get too excited.

496
00:47:34.269 --> 00:47:36.889
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:47:36.980 --> 00:47:39.019
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:47:39.099 --> 00:47:43.730
Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:47:43.820 --> 00:47:45.690
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:47:45.739 --> 00:47:48.780
Want to breed?

501
00:47:48.860 --> 00:47:51.869
Tempting. but no.

502
00:47:54.789 --> 00:47:56.750
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:47:56.789 --> 00:47:58.750
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:47:58.789 --> 00:48:01.960
Hey! Come along!

505
00:48:02.039 --> 00:48:04.630
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:48:04.710 --> 00:48:07.420
Gather pall these babies.

507
00:48:07.510 --> 00:48:09.760
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

508
00:48:13.510 --> 00:48:15.639
That's not the one.

509
00:48:19.349 --> 00:48:22.099
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:48:22.190 --> 00:48:24.769
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:48:24.860 --> 00:48:26.440
No! Don't let her!

512
00:48:26.530 --> 00:48:27.989
Aah!

513
00:48:28.070 --> 00:48:30.949
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:48:40.289 --> 00:48:43.750
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:48:43.840 --> 00:48:47.170
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:48:49.760 --> 00:48:52.260
You're no woman!

517
00:48:52.340 --> 00:48:54.179
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

518
00:48:54.260 --> 00:48:57.139
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:48:57.179 --> 00:48:59.980
Meet Llug.

520
00:49:01.269 --> 00:49:03.309
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:49:09.610 --> 00:49:10.860
- To the horses!

522
00:49:10.860 --> 00:49:11.949
To the horses!

523
00:49:14.489 --> 00:49:16.949
Hey! What are you doing?

524
00:49:21.329 --> 00:49:23.250
Hyah!

525
00:49:23.329 --> 00:49:27.250
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

526
00:49:30.719 --> 00:49:35.599
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

527
00:49:35.679 --> 00:49:38.059
Don't let them get away!

528
00:49:39.719 --> 00:49:43.139
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

529
00:49:54.949 --> 00:49:56.989
Hyah!

530
00:50:02.119 --> 00:50:04.619
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

531
00:50:06.670 --> 00:50:10.340
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

532
00:50:33.739 --> 00:50:36.070
Madmartigan!
Stop!

533
00:51:06.139 --> 00:51:08.190
Franjean. help me!

534
00:51:12.820 --> 00:51:14.739
- Rool!
- Help!

535
00:51:14.820 --> 00:51:17.860
Rool! Rool.

536
00:51:19.030 --> 00:51:22.829
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

537
00:51:28.210 --> 00:51:30.460
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

538
00:51:30.539 --> 00:51:33.000
Yeah. pull!

539
00:51:51.190 --> 00:51:53.190
You can't have her!

540
00:51:59.110 --> 00:52:00.820
Whoa!

541
00:52:05.539 --> 00:52:09.119
Rool. this isn't funny!

542
00:52:09.210 --> 00:52:11.130
Help me cut the rope!

543
00:52:24.309 --> 00:52:27.059
Who-oa!

544
00:52:48.579 --> 00:52:51.170
Willow. stay down!

545
00:52:54.880 --> 00:52:56.920
Whoa!

546
00:52:56.960 --> 00:52:59.219
Whoa!

547
00:52:59.300 --> 00:53:01.219
Gone crazy?

548
00:53:01.300 --> 00:53:03.429
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

549
00:53:03.510 --> 00:53:05.929
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

550
00:53:05.969 --> 00:53:08.599
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

551
00:53:31.409 --> 00:53:33.920
Whoa! Whoa!

552
00:53:37.090 --> 00:53:39.420
Oh. Rool.

553
00:53:39.510 --> 00:53:43.179
Now we stop. peck.

554
00:53:43.260 --> 00:53:48.559
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

555
00:53:48.599 --> 00:53:52.809
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

556
00:53:54.309 --> 00:53:56.809
I just saved that infant's life!

557
00:53:58.269 --> 00:54:00.610
Hah! Hah!

558
00:54:00.690 --> 00:54:02.650
Gather your wits. Come on.

559
00:54:02.699 --> 00:54:05.739
- Don't worry about me.
- Come on!

560
00:54:06.820 --> 00:54:08.989
Get down!

561
00:54:09.079 --> 00:54:11.449
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

562
00:54:13.369 --> 00:54:15.460
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

563
00:54:31.969 --> 00:54:34.559
- Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

564
00:54:34.639 --> 00:54:36.099
Before those troops come back.

565
00:54:36.150 --> 00:54:39.610
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

566
00:54:48.030 --> 00:54:50.119
Madmartigan. wait!

567
00:54:50.159 --> 00:54:53.500
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

568
00:54:53.579 --> 00:54:55.539
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

569
00:54:55.619 --> 00:54:58.840
My help? What do 
you need my help for?

570
00:54:58.920 --> 00:55:01.090
You're a sorcerer!

571
00:55:01.170 --> 00:55:04.380
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

572
00:55:04.469 --> 00:55:07.340
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

573
00:55:07.429 --> 00:55:10.679
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

574
00:55:13.929 --> 00:55:18.860
Hurry! Big dogs!

575
00:55:18.940 --> 00:55:23.190
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

576
00:55:23.230 --> 00:55:25.190
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

577
00:55:39.380 --> 00:55:42.210
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

578
00:55:43.710 --> 00:55:47.340
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

579
00:55:48.380 --> 00:55:51.550
That way.

580
00:55:51.599 --> 00:55:55.219
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

581
00:55:55.309 --> 00:55:57.230
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

582
00:55:57.309 --> 00:55:59.519
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

583
00:55:59.599 --> 00:56:01.610
That way!

584
00:56:04.650 --> 00:56:09.199
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

585
00:56:09.239 --> 00:56:12.239
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

586
00:56:12.329 --> 00:56:14.539
But that's it!

587
00:56:14.579 --> 00:56:18.369
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

588
00:56:18.409 --> 00:56:23.590
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

589
00:56:23.670 --> 00:56:26.300
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

590
00:56:33.010 --> 00:56:37.679
Kael. have you found the child?

591
00:56:37.769 --> 00:56:39.519
The search goes on. my queen.

592
00:56:40.599 --> 00:56:42.610
Why. with my powers.

593
00:56:42.690 --> 00:56:45.900
with the strength
of my great army.

594
00:56:45.980 --> 00:56:49.400
can you not find
one little child?

595
00:56:49.449 --> 00:56:51.780
We look even now.
It won't be long.

596
00:56:51.860 --> 00:56:55.239
Find the child.
Find the child!

597
00:56:55.280 --> 00:56:57.909
Time is running out.

598
00:57:02.079 --> 00:57:06.500
Good night.

599
00:57:06.550 --> 00:57:09.880
She is kinda cute.

600
00:57:09.969 --> 00:57:11.719
When she's quiet.

601
00:57:13.139 --> 00:57:15.050
She's really a princess.

602
00:57:15.139 --> 00:57:19.139
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

603
00:57:19.230 --> 00:57:21.139
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

604
00:57:21.230 --> 00:57:25.019
Go to sleep. Willow.

605
00:57:25.110 --> 00:57:27.610
Good night. Madmartigan.

606
00:57:27.650 --> 00:57:30.650
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

607
00:57:30.699 --> 00:57:34.030
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

608
00:57:34.119 --> 00:57:37.030
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

609
00:57:47.840 --> 00:57:50.550
Tuatha...

610
00:57:50.630 --> 00:57:52.800
Lawkathok...

611
00:57:52.880 --> 00:57:54.800
Tuatha!

612
00:57:54.840 --> 00:57:57.599
Huh?
Willow?

613
00:57:58.679 --> 00:58:00.809
Willow?

614
00:58:02.559 --> 00:58:05.019
Oh. There you are.

615
00:58:05.099 --> 00:58:07.059
Madmartigan!

616
00:58:07.150 --> 00:58:10.480
'Night. Willow.

617
00:58:22.579 --> 00:58:24.579
This way! This way!

618
00:58:36.389 --> 00:58:38.349
What are you doing?

619
00:58:38.389 --> 00:58:40.769
I found some black root.
She loves it!

620
00:58:40.849 --> 00:58:43.769
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

621
00:58:43.849 --> 00:58:45.849
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

622
00:58:46.019 --> 00:58:49.070
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

623
00:58:49.150 --> 00:58:51.690
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

624
00:58:51.780 --> 00:58:54.530
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

625
00:58:54.623 --> 00:58:57.583
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

626
00:58:57.623 --> 00:58:59.962
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

627
00:59:04.132 --> 00:59:06.172
Did you see what he did?

628
00:59:06.262 --> 00:59:09.512
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

629
00:59:14.353 --> 00:59:17.692
There it is! The island!

630
00:59:19.902 --> 00:59:21.813
We made it.

631
00:59:21.902 --> 00:59:26.442
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

632
00:59:26.532 --> 00:59:30.782
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

633
00:59:48.842 --> 00:59:50.842
Well. looks like
I got you here.

634
00:59:50.932 --> 00:59:53.392
You!
What did you do?

635
00:59:53.472 --> 00:59:56.472
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

636
00:59:56.563 --> 00:59:58.522
I found a boat.
We're all set.

637
00:59:58.603 --> 01:00:02.522
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

638
01:00:02.612 --> 01:00:05.942
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

639
01:00:08.032 --> 01:00:10.702
Your mother was lizard!

640
01:00:13.702 --> 01:00:16.202
Good-bye. Sticks.

641
01:00:18.873 --> 01:00:21.792
If you really are a princess.

642
01:00:21.873 --> 01:00:24.842
take care of him.

643
01:00:31.182 --> 01:00:34.472
- Madmartigan!
- What?

644
01:00:34.552 --> 01:00:36.432
Thanks.

645
01:00:45.942 --> 01:00:48.482
Hey! Aah!

646
01:00:48.532 --> 01:00:51.902
- Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

647
01:00:53.072 --> 01:00:56.083
It's all right. Blora.

648
01:00:56.162 --> 01:00:58.583
Go to sleep.

649
01:00:58.662 --> 01:01:01.002
Nobody'll find you here.

650
01:01:01.083 --> 01:01:02.672
I'll be back with
Fin Raziel very soon.

651
01:01:02.712 --> 01:01:06.042
We will guard her
with our meagre lives.

652
01:01:34.362 --> 01:01:37.202
Raziel!

653
01:01:37.282 --> 01:01:41.083
Fin Raziel!
I have to talk to you. please!

654
01:01:45.002 --> 01:01:47.592
Raziel!

655
01:01:52.422 --> 01:01:56.092
She's not here.

656
01:01:59.103 --> 01:02:01.022
Aah!

657
01:02:01.103 --> 01:02:04.642
Get back! Who are you?

658
01:02:05.772 --> 01:02:08.652
Who are you?

659
01:02:11.072 --> 01:02:14.152
- I'm Willow Ufgood.
- What are you doing here?

660
01:02:14.242 --> 01:02:17.912
I've come to find the great
sorceress. Fin Raziel.

661
01:02:17.992 --> 01:02:20.583
That's me!
I'm Raziel!

662
01:02:22.623 --> 01:02:24.542
This can't be right!

663
01:02:24.623 --> 01:02:28.132
One of Bavmorda's spells
transformed me.

664
01:02:30.422 --> 01:02:33.012
Believe me. it could
have been worse!

665
01:02:33.092 --> 01:02:38.892
Oh. Well. this wand is for you.
It's from Cherlindrea.

666
01:02:38.972 --> 01:02:43.472
Then the prophecy is true.
The princess has been born.

667
01:02:43.563 --> 01:02:45.522
Take me to her.

668
01:02:48.063 --> 01:02:50.822
It is Blora Danan.

669
01:02:50.902 --> 01:02:53.822
Isn't she beautiful?

670
01:02:53.902 --> 01:02:56.862
Isn't she beautiful?

671
01:02:56.952 --> 01:03:00.452
- That's Raziel?
- I don't know. I-

672
01:03:00.532 --> 01:03:02.792
I expected something
more grand. Less. uh-

673
01:03:02.833 --> 01:03:04.792
- Fuzzy.
- Fuzzy!

674
01:03:04.873 --> 01:03:08.672
You must use the wand.
Turn me back into my human form.

675
01:03:08.752 --> 01:03:12.092
- What do I do?
- You mean you're not a sorcerer?

676
01:03:13.302 --> 01:03:15.802
Yes. Sort a.

677
01:03:15.882 --> 01:03:18.382
I'm a farmer.

678
01:03:18.472 --> 01:03:20.392
But I do know a few tricks.

679
01:03:20.432 --> 01:03:25.982
Tricks? Cherlindrea sent you?
You must learn real magic.

680
01:03:26.103 --> 01:03:30.152
Horses! Horses!

681
01:03:30.232 --> 01:03:32.732
Quick! Take her!
Hurry! Hurry!

682
01:03:41.532 --> 01:03:44.492
I knew he was a traitor!

683
01:03:47.083 --> 01:03:49.792
- Sorry about this. peck.
- Keep your mouth shut!

684
01:03:50.833 --> 01:03:53.632
Told you we'd find him
without your help.

685
01:03:53.712 --> 01:03:55.672
- Give me that baby.
- No!

686
01:03:59.132 --> 01:04:03.103
- Give her back!
- Leave me alone! Don't touch me!

687
01:04:09.022 --> 01:04:10.902
This is the one
we're looking for.

688
01:04:10.982 --> 01:04:14.362
We must take it back to Nockmaar.

689
01:04:17.152 --> 01:04:19.072
Lose your skirt?

690
01:04:26.742 --> 01:04:28.702
I've still got what counts.

691
01:04:28.752 --> 01:04:31.083
Not for long.

692
01:04:36.922 --> 01:04:40.472
- Bring him.
- Over here!

693
01:04:58.152 --> 01:05:00.902
We'll never keep up
with those horses.

694
01:05:00.952 --> 01:05:02.912
Then we will
have to track them.

695
01:05:02.952 --> 01:05:04.373
That would take forever.

696
01:05:04.452 --> 01:05:07.202
Besides. even if we find them.
they'll catch us.

697
01:05:07.242 --> 01:05:10.452
stick us in cages. torture us
and finally devour us.

698
01:05:10.542 --> 01:05:12.502
Are you suggesting
we go home?

699
01:05:12.583 --> 01:05:15.502
- Nah. This is more fun!
- All right.

700
01:05:15.592 --> 01:05:17.502
Fine. then.
Come on!

701
01:05:31.313 --> 01:05:34.772
I'm worried about Blora.
She doesn't sound good.

702
01:05:34.813 --> 01:05:37.612
Hurry! Practice
the chant I taught you!

703
01:05:37.652 --> 01:05:43.452
Tanna... looatha- Oh. I can't
remember the middle part.

704
01:05:43.532 --> 01:05:45.572
Locktwaar!

705
01:05:45.623 --> 01:05:48.623
That's the word
that pleads for change.

706
01:05:48.702 --> 01:05:50.662
Locktwaar.

707
01:05:54.333 --> 01:05:57.502
Blora's cold and hungry.
She knows me.

708
01:05:57.592 --> 01:05:59.502
Please. let me
take care of her.

709
01:05:59.592 --> 01:06:01.712
I don't need help
from a peck.

710
01:06:05.472 --> 01:06:09.512
- What are you staring at?
- Your leg.

711
01:06:09.603 --> 01:06:11.972
I'd like to break it.

712
01:06:12.022 --> 01:06:16.902
You may find that difficult while
I'm up here and you're down there.

713
01:06:20.022 --> 01:06:22.242
I hate that woman.

714
01:06:54.892 --> 01:06:56.982
Hyah!

715
01:07:00.772 --> 01:07:03.572
I found it. Kael.

716
01:07:04.692 --> 01:07:07.742
That should make
my mother happy.

717
01:07:07.822 --> 01:07:10.833
What are they gonna do to her?

718
01:07:23.382 --> 01:07:26.052
Hither walha...

719
01:07:26.132 --> 01:07:29.682
bairn derubordak...

720
01:07:29.762 --> 01:07:31.682
bellanockt.

721
01:07:31.762 --> 01:07:34.642
That's magic?
Smells terrible.

722
01:07:34.722 --> 01:07:37.942
- It's the life spark. It forms after-
- Well. it stinks!

723
01:07:38.022 --> 01:07:41.192
- This whole thing stinks!
- Ignore him. Willow.

724
01:07:41.272 --> 01:07:44.282
- He's a fool!
- If only I had a sword!

725
01:07:44.362 --> 01:07:47.452
If only you'd quit talking about it.

726
01:07:47.532 --> 01:07:50.912
Willow. you must transform me
to my human self.

727
01:07:50.952 --> 01:07:53.782
But. Raziel.
I'm not ready yet.

728
01:07:53.873 --> 01:07:57.083
You'd better be.
Get me down.

729
01:08:00.712 --> 01:08:03.132
Ow!

730
01:08:05.762 --> 01:08:08.762
Why don't you help me get out of here
instead of chattering with that muskrat?

731
01:08:08.842 --> 01:08:11.592
Muskrat!
When I change back...

732
01:08:11.642 --> 01:08:15.603
to my former self.
I will crush this army.

733
01:08:15.682 --> 01:08:18.353
and take Blora Danan
to Tir Asleen...

734
01:08:18.432 --> 01:08:21.023
where she will be safe.

735
01:08:21.103 --> 01:08:23.443
Ow!

736
01:08:23.483 --> 01:08:25.443
What'd you bite me for?

737
01:08:25.483 --> 01:08:28.823
You need three drops
of your blood to put in the potion.

738
01:08:28.903 --> 01:08:32.202
Well. you coulda warned me.

739
01:08:32.282 --> 01:08:34.702
For beginners.
there's some pain.

740
01:08:34.782 --> 01:08:39.872
but don't let anything
break your concentration.

741
01:08:45.002 --> 01:08:47.882
